## SDD Phase → Board Update Map

When an SDD phase completes, update the board as follows:

| SDD Phase Completes | Status | SDD Phase |
|---------------------|--------|-----------|
| explore | In Progress (`47fc9ee4`) | Explore (`cbe57d4d`) |
| propose | In Progress (`47fc9ee4`) | Propose (`f7b5e3ad`) |
| spec | In Progress (`47fc9ee4`) | Spec (`215b5bd3`) |
| design | In Progress (`47fc9ee4`) | Design (`8a8f0ea4`) |
| tasks | In Progress (`47fc9ee4`) | Tasks (`1b7d843f`) |
| apply | In Progress (`47fc9ee4`) | Apply (`e827dc3f`) |
| verify | In Progress (`47fc9ee4`) | Verify (`8242b830`) |
| archive | Done (`98236657`) | Done (`ce5c9fcc`) |

## Commands

### Update an item's Status

```bash
gh project item-edit \
  --id <ITEM_ID> \
  --field-id PVTSSF_lADOEeFGTc4Bc5CtzhXejII \
  --project-id PVT_kwDOEeFGTc4Bc5Ct \
  --single-select-option-id <OPTION_ID>
```

### Update an item's SDD Phase

```bash
gh project item-edit \
  --id <ITEM_ID> \
  --field-id PVTSSF_lADOEeFGTc4Bc5CtzhYUpaI \
  --project-id PVT_kwDOEeFGTc4Bc5Ct \
  --single-select-option-id <PHASE_OPTION_ID>
```

### Add an issue to the project board

```bash
gh project item-add 2 --owner reverberage --url <ISSUE_URL>
```

### Find an item ID from an issue number

```bash
gh api graphql -f query='query{organization(login:"reverberage"){projectV2(number:2){items(first:100){nodes{id content{...on Issue{number}}}}}}}' --jq '.data.organization.projectV2.items.nodes[] | select(.content.number == <ISSUE_NUMBER>) | .id'
```

Replace `<ISSUE_NUMBER>` with the actual issue number.

## Workflow: After SDD Phase Completion

After `memory_save` succeeds in any SDD phase skill, update the board:

1. Find the item ID for the issue
2. Update both Status and SDD Phase fields
3. Skip silently if the issue is not on the board

## Rules

- NEVER update the board before the memory_save succeeds. The board is downstream of MAGI.
- If `ITEM_ID` is empty (issue not on board), skip the update — do NOT fail the task.
- Always update both Status AND SDD Phase together for consistency.
- All commands use `--owner reverberage`, never `--org`.
